Agreeing to our Terms of Service
Date Last Modified: April 2024
The
ed.voicethread.com
and
voicethread.com
websites (the “
Websites
”), the VoiceThread mobile applications (the “
Apps
”), and the related online and mobile services (collectively with the Website and the App, the “
Services
”) are made available by VoiceThread Inc., a Delaware corporation (“
VoiceThread
”), subject to these Terms and Conditions. Certain provisions in the proceeding paragraphs may only apply to certain portions of the Services.
By accessing any part of the Services, you are agreeing to the Terms and Conditions described below (the “
Terms and Conditions
” or “
Terms
”) AND THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF OUR
PRIVACY NOTICE
(the “Privacy Notice”), WHICH ARE INCORPORATED HEREIN BY REFERENCE. If you do not agree to any of these Terms, you should not use the Services. If you are otherwise engaged with VoiceThread for specific Services through a subsequent agreement, that agreement shall control and supersede these Terms and Conditions.
PLEASE READ THESE TERMS AND CONDITIONS CAREFULLY. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO THESE TERMS AND CONDITIONS, DO NOT DOWNLOAD THE APPS OR CONTINUE TO ACCESS OR USE THE SERVICES AND DO NOT REGISTER FOR AN ACCOUNT.
These Terms and Conditions apply to all Users, including Users who are simply viewing content available via the Service, Users utilizing free Services, and Users who have engaged for paid Services. Users include, but are not limited to, students, parents, educators, academic institutions, or administrators (collectively, “
Users,
” “you” and through similar words such as “your,” etc.). Not all Terms shall apply to all types of Users where specified in the Terms and Conditions. Please note, these Terms and Conditions are offered in multiple languages consistent with the version of the platform you are using. To ensure you are viewing in the appropriate language, please review these Terms as connected via your instance of the platform.
If you are under the age of 13, you are not permitted to register for an Account (defined below) on the Services.
Registering or creating an account on the K-12 focused service ed.voicethread.com may only be completed, or facilitated by, an educator, school administrator, or other school official.
If you are a member of an organization, such as a school district, university, or other, similar educational institution, your organization may have engaged VoiceThread under a separate written agreement. Such agreement is separate from these Terms and Conditions and, in the event such agreement conflicts with these Terms and Conditions, that agreement shall control and supersede these Terms and Conditions. If you are entering into these Terms and Conditions on behalf of your organization, you represent that you have the authority to bind such entity to these Terms and Conditions. If you do not have such authority or otherwise do not agree to these Terms and Conditions, you should not use or access the Services. You must be a grade school educator or administrator to register for the portion of the Services available on ed.voicethread.com.
We reserve the right to refuse a User’s access to the Service for any reason, at our sole discretion. In addition, at our sole discretion, we may suspend or terminate a User’s Account (described below) for any reason. Such termination of your Account will result in your loss of access to the Services. We will not be liable for any decision to suspend, terminate or refuse service under any circumstances.
The Service is controlled and offered by us from our facilities in the United States of America. Except as indicated in these Terms and the
Privacy Notice
, we make no representations that the Service is appropriate or available for use in other locations. Those who access or use the Service from other jurisdictions do so at their own volition and are responsible for compliance with local law.
1. Compliance
To ensure you remain in compliance with these Terms and Conditions, VoiceThread recommends reviewing the current Terms and Conditions each time you access or use the Services. All access to and use of the Services and Accounts (including, but not limited to, the materials, content, information, and data contained on or provided through the Services and Accounts) are subject to compliance with these Terms and Conditions and all applicable laws, rules, and regulations. If you have any questions or comments regarding these Terms and Conditions or the Services, please contact VoiceThread at the contact information listed below. In addition, if you would like to report violations of these Terms and Conditions (including but not limited to violations by an individual User), please utilize the contact information listed below.
2. General Use
The Services are made available to you for your personal (noncommercial) and/or educational use and are subject to these Terms and Conditions, to allow you to (i) obtain information about the Services, (ii) register for an Account, and (iii) engage with the various interactive properties available on the Services. Subject to these Terms and Conditions, VoiceThread grants you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, and revocable license to download, access, and use the Services solely for the applicable purposes described in these Terms and Conditions and for your personal, non-commercial benefit. Except as otherwise expressly set forth herein, you shall have no other rights to the Services, and no other rights shall be implied.
3. Visitors to the Service and Account Creation
You may be able to visit certain public sections of the Services without identifying yourself or providing personal information. In order to access some features of the Services, you are required to register with the Services and select a username and password (create an “
Account
”). By registering for an Account, you represent and warrant that all registration information you submit is truthful and accurate. You may not have more than one (1) Account without VoiceThread’s permission, and you must access the Services and non-public portions of the Websites and Apps through your Account. The security and confidentiality of your Account username and password is your sole responsibility. You shall ensure that no unauthorized person shall have access to your Account, username, or password and shall immediately notify VoiceThread of any unauthorized access or use of which you become aware. You may not transfer your Account to anyone without the express prior written consent of VoiceThread. You agree to bear all responsibility and liability for all actions under or through your Account as well as all fees and/or charges incurred from the use of your Account, whether authorized or unauthorized. You may update your Account by changing the Account settings.
If you would like to delete your Account, you may do so at any time by contacting VoiceThread as described herein. When you delete your Account or a student’s Account, we delete the profile information and any other content those Accounts have provided to the Service. Information that you have shared with others, others have shared about you, or content others may have copied is not part of your Account and may not be deleted when you delete your Account. If you are an educator or school administrator using the ed.voicethread.com portion of the Services, you may delete any Account(s) you have administrative control over by logging into the management portal associated with your Account.
4. Registration Data
All of your information and data provided to VoiceThread in connection with registering for your Account (“
Registration Data
”) must be true, accurate, current, and complete at all times, and it is your responsibility to immediately update your Registration Data should any changes occur in order to keep it true, accurate, current, and complete. If you provide any information that is untrue, inaccurate, or incomplete, or if VoiceThread has reasonable grounds to suspect that such information is untrue, inaccurate, or incomplete, VoiceThread has the right to suspend or terminate your Account as described in these Terms. If you are registering for Accounts of behalf of others (e.g., an educator registering on behalf of students), you warrant that the appropriate permissions and authorizations have been received prior to such registration.
Notwithstanding anything to the contrary, you hereby authorize VoiceThread and its affiliates, contractors, and suppliers to use, copy, sublicense, and disclose Registration Data (i) as part of providing the Services; (ii) if required by applicable law, where necessary to enforce these Terms and Conditions, and/or to protect any of VoiceThread’s or other parties’ legal rights; (iii) in an aggregated form which does not include your identifying information; and (iv) as permitted by VoiceThread’s
Privacy Notice
. You are solely responsible for obtaining any necessary rights, authorizations, and/or consents with respect to your Registration Data, including, without limitation, to grant the foregoing rights to VoiceThread and its affiliates, contractors, and suppliers. If you provide VoiceThread your email address, you hereby consent to and authorize VoiceThread to (a) send notices regarding the Services to such email address, instead of notice by other means such as mail, and (b) send other messages to such email address, such as changes to features of the Services and special offers (collectively, “
Other Messages
”). If you do not want to receive Other Messages, you may opt out in the available email communications settings. Opting out of receiving Other Messages may prevent you from receiving email messages regarding updates, changes to the Services or offers.
