The license you grant to VoiceThread to reproduce, copy, use, host, store, sublicense, reproduce, create derivative works from, modify, publish, edit, translate, distribute, perform and display User Content will terminate when (i) you delete such User Content with intellectual property rights, (ii) you or your organization deletes any personal information that may be considered User Content, or (iii) you delete your Account. If your content has been shared with others, and they have not deleted it or removed others’ access to it, then such User Content may still be available on the Services. When you delete User Content, Education Records, or personal information, it will be deleted in a manner similar to moving it to the recycle or trash folder on your computer or device. “Undo” features may be available for certain deletion events to enable deletion errors to be rectified before data is irretrievably lost, and, as such, deleted content may persist in backup copies for a reasonable period of time, though such deleted content will not be available to other Users. For more information, please see our
