Privacy Notice
Date Last Updated: April 2024
VoiceThread services, including (without limitation) our websites
ed.voicethread.com
and
voicethread.com
, the VoiceThread mobile applications, and other interactive properties through which the services are delivered (collectively, the “Services”) are owned, operated and distributed by VoiceThread (referred to in this Privacy Notice as “VoiceThread” or “we” and through similar words such as “us,” “our,” etc.). This Privacy Notice outlines the personal information that VoiceThread may collect, how VoiceThread uses and safeguards that information, with whom we may share it, and your resources. The proceeding paragraphs may not be applicable to certain portions of the Services. The category of information that VoiceThread collects and how it’s used may vary depending on which website or feature of the Services you are utilizing.
While VoiceThread is available internationally and provided in a manner compliant with international privacy laws,
THIS SERVICE IS OFFERED FROM THE UNITED STATES (“US”)
and VoiceThread is a US-based company. If you use the Service, all information, including personal information, will be transferred to VoiceThread in the US and used as described in this Privacy Notice. Specific and detailed information about use internationally, including General Data Protection Regulation ("GDPR"), can be found below.
While this policy applies broadly to all Users, specific guidance around children’s Personal Information, including exceptions to the general rules of personal information stated herein, can be found in the section labeled Children’s Privacy.
VoiceThread encourages our students, administrators, educators, customers, visitors, business associates, and any other interested parties to read this Privacy Notice, which applies to all Users. While VoiceThread makes every effort to maintain the accuracy of the personal information it holds through a variety of methods, the primary method for ensuring accurate data is facilitating your ability to correct the personal information we hold about you as described in this Notice. As such, we also encourage our Users to frequently review and update their personal information to ensure its accuracy. All corrections to personal information are made immediately upon submission, unless confirmation with the school or other parties is necessary in which case it could take up to 45 days, as defined by applicable privacy laws.
By using our Service or submitting personal information to VoiceThread by any other means, you acknowledge that you understand and agree to be bound by this Privacy Notice, and agree that VoiceThread may collect, process, transfer, use, and disclose your personal information as described in this Notice. Further, by accessing any part of the Service, you are agreeing to THE TERMS OF OUR TERMS AND CONDITIONS (the “Terms and Conditions”). IF YOU DO NOT AGREE WITH ANY PART OF THIS PRIVACY NOTICE OR OUR TERMS AND CONDITIONS, PLEASE DO NOT USE ANY PORTION OF THE SERVICES. Please note, this Privacy Notice is offered in multiple languages consistent with the version of the platform you are using. To ensure you are viewing in the appropriate language, please review this Notice as connected via your instance of the platform.
VoiceThread asserts no ownership rights over the personal information submitted via the Service, and such data ownership rights are retained by the individual Users or, in certain cases, the institutions with which individual Users are associated (e.g., schools, universities, school districts). VoiceThread does retain certain data licenses in order to provide the Services as described in the Terms and Conditions.
What personal information do we collect about you?
Personal information (also commonly known as personally identifiable information (PII) or personal data) is information that can be used to identify you, or any other individual to whom the information may relate. The types and amounts of information collected vary depending on whether you are a student, parent, educator, or school administrator. We will only collect, use, and share your personal information in accordance with this Privacy Notice.
The personal information that we may collect directly from those registering for the Service, includes the following categories:
Name and contact information (e.g. address; phone number; email);
Biometric data is not collected;
Account and Profile Information (e.g. password, profile picture);
Student and Class Information (e.g. class year, names of students, identity name);
School Information (e.g. school name, address, administrator contact);
Billing Information (e.g. credit card, bank account, billing contact information);
Order Information (e.g. current order/purchase information, purchase history, shipping details);
Company/employer information;
Geolocation and geotracking data is never collected. Regional location data may captured and stored for security, infrastructure, and customization use and planning but is never sold to any third parties;
Information contained in posts you make on the public forums and interactive features of the Service;
Information in our
Cookie Policy
, the degree to which such information is defined as personal information under the laws of a particular jurisdiction;
Other information that may be exchanged in the course of engaging with the Service. You will be aware of any subsequently collected information because it will come directly from you.
For the avoidance of doubt, any data (whether such data alone is considered personal or non-personal information) combined with or associated with your name or other identifier specific to you shall be treated as your personal information.
The Services are not intended to support the processing of health information (i.e. Personal Health Information (PHI)) as defined and protected under the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA). As such, VoiceThread does not collect PHI and Users should not use the Services to upload, store, or otherwise process PHI.
VoiceThread is committed to providing you with easy ways to access, update, correct, or delete your information. You may access the personal information that VoiceThread has collected by accessing your information through your account or by contacting us as described herein. There are certain instances where VoiceThread may not be able to guarantee complete access due to legal restrictions or fulfill requests that are unreasonably difficult, repetitive, or impractical.
Collection of User Generated Content
The Service enables Users to post content on the Service, including your comments and any other information that you would like to be available on the Service, which may become public (“User Content”). User Content may include uploaded media (images, videos, presentations, documents, etc.), comments on uploaded media, reviews of the Services, messaging in private comments, and posts on public forums or discussion boards. If you do post content, all of the information that you post will be available to authorized personnel of VoiceThread and may be made available to the public as permitted by the capabilities of the Service and at your discretion. VoiceThread utilizes a cloud infrastructure to store and back-up any content uploaded to the Services. You expressly acknowledge and agree that we may access in real-time, record, and store archives of any User Content on our servers to make use of them in connection with your use of the Service. You retain all ownership rights in User Content as described in the Terms and Conditions, though VoiceThread may retain certain, limited license to use such User Content (though VoiceThread does NOT retain Copyright License). For more information about the license retained by VoiceThread, and when such license terminates, please review the Terms and Conditions. If you submit a review, recommendation, endorsement, or other User Content through the Service, or through other websites including Facebook, Instagram, Google, Yelp, and other similar channels, we may share that review, recommendation, endorsement, or content publicly on the Service.
No educator, school administrator, parent, or student profiles are made available to the general public through the Services. However, Users may choose to share information or content through the Services via publishing or sharing work they have created (such as VoiceThread conversations, participating in public Threadboxes, or submitting content to our Digital Library or other public venues for content). Please keep in mind that information (including your personal information or children's personal information) or content that you voluntarily disclose to others (including to other VoiceThread Users you interact with through the Service) can, like all digital information that appears on a screen, be viewed, copied, stored, and used by the people you share it with. We cannot control the actions of people with whom you choose to share information.
As an educator or school administrator, you can invite your students’ parents or outside subject matter experts to view or even comment on your students’ work. We will collect and store the names, email addresses, and phone numbers of those people, and those items will be treated as personal information in accordance with this Privacy Notice. If any individual that has been invited to the Services would like to remove their information from the system, they may contact VoiceThread as described herein.
Children’s Privacy
The Services provided by VoiceThread are designed to be suitable for education use in an academic setting, among other uses, and, as a result, children’s personal information may be collected. If you are under the age of 13, you are not permitted to register for an account on the Service or the Websites. You may only access and use the Services if an account has been created for you by an educator at your school. If you are under the age of 18, you are not permitted to register for an account on ed.voicethread.com and may only access and use the portion of the Services available on ed.voicethread.com if an account has been created on your behalf by an educator at your school. Before providing student access to any of the Services, VoiceThread obtains parental consent and/or relies on the parental consent obtained by a school or educator prior to student data being uploaded. Any such consent shall be consistent with the requirements of the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (“COPPA”) for students under the age of 13. You may inquire with your school or with VoiceThread via the contact information in this Notice to understand how consent for a particular student is managed. If VoiceThread receives notice or discovers independently that information of a child under the age of 13 was collected without parental consent, that child’s personal information will be promptly deleted if consent cannot be confirmed or obtained within a reasonable time.
The portion of the Services available on ed.voicethread.com are dedicated for use with grade school students and educators. By themselves, children cannot create accounts on ed.voicethread.com; only school personnel may do so. As such, VoiceThread does not receive information directly from children, and we rely solely on school personnel to provide identity data about students. ed.voicethread.com requires a student’s educators and school administrators to have control and visibility over that student’s work. No student profile or student work is made available or visible to the public or to any other students by default, but educators may allow their students to share their work with other students, educators, school administrators in their school, and beyond. The option to share such student information is at the discretion of the educator, and students and parents should inquire with the educator about such sharing. In addition, Educators may share their own work with other students, educators, school administrators in their school, and beyond. Special controls available on the ed.voicethread.com portion of the Services include controls that allow school personnel to implement age-appropriate and individually appropriate sharing and publishing policies. For assistance on these control features, please see our
FAQ
on the subject or contact us as described herein.
There is a “
two-level-identity-policy
” available for students that allows a student’s identity name and image to be anonymized as locally appropriate while ensuring that all educators and administrators within the same school or district license can see the true name of the student. This two-level-identity system enables more schools to opt to allow their students to collaborate and publish with the appropriate level of anonymity, while also ensuring that students are working within a transparent environment. Educators may deploy this method when registering for student accounts.
VoiceThread abides by its
Student Privacy Pledge
in an effort to protect children’s information. As provided in this pledge, VoiceThread commits itself to periodic examinations of the security infrastructure and privacy practices, as well as compliance with the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (“FERPA”), the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (“COPPA”), this Privacy Notice, and our
Terms and Conditions
.
What are the sources of personal information collected by VoiceThread?
When providing personal information to VoiceThread as described in this Notice, that personal information is collected directly from you, and you will know the precise personal information being collected by us. In addition, as indicated in this Privacy Notice, certain personal information may be collected from educators or school administrators in order to facilitate student access to the Services.
VoiceThread does not collect personal information from any other sources, except where it may automatically be collected by third-party service providers, e.g. analytics, security, and infrastructure monitoring services, though such collection will always be within the context of the Service.
