Other than as described herein, VoiceThread will not disclose your personal information for any purpose without your consent. VoiceThread is committed to transparency in its data privacy practices ensuring that you can make meaningful choices about how your personal information is used. For example, you may be able to opt-out of providing certain information, access and manage your account information within your account, control who you share information with, and delete or otherwise remove information. However, certain information must be provided in order for VoiceThread to provide the Services. Such information might include a valid email address or the name of the school you attend or are affiliated with.
How does VoiceThread share your personal information with third parties?
We may provide any of the described categories of personal information to VoiceThread employees, consultants, affiliates or other businesses or persons for the purpose of processing such information on our behalf in order to provide the Service to you. In such circumstances, we require that these parties agree to protect the confidentiality of such information consistent with the terms of this Privacy Notice, as well as comply with applicable laws and provide the same security protections as VoiceThread, including but not limited to adherence to deletion and other available requests. Third parties receiving personal information may include:
Third-party vendors or service providers providing crucial services and necessary to provide the Services to you (e.g. emailing on behalf of VoiceThread, database management services, database hosting, customer support software, and security);
Business partners, contractors, channel partners, subsidiaries, or other affiliated entities for specific purposes consistent with this Privacy Notice;
